  "feedback": "## ATX Review — issue-786-integration-icons-add-button\n\n**Overall rating: 3/5** (gui-routes 4/5, test-coverage 3/5)\n**No blockers. 5 warnings, 6 suggestions.**\n\n---\n\n### Warnings\n\n| # | File | Finding |\n|---|------|---------|\n| W1 | `integration-icon.tsx:28-35` | Fallback `\u003cdiv\u003e` uses `aria-label` without `role=\"img\"`. AT behaviour on `aria-label` on a generic div is inconsistent — some readers announce it, others ignore it. |\n| W2 | `integration-card.test.tsx:20-111` | The badge→icon swap (this PR's central card change) is **unguarded**. Existing assertions match the type label `\u003cspan\u003e`, not the removed badge, so reverting `\u003cIntegrationIcon\u003e` to a two-letter badge wouldn't fail a single test. |\n| W3 | `integration-icon.test.tsx:21-24` | Fallback branch covered by only one input (`'custom'`). Edge cases `\"\"`, `\"x\"`, and `size`/`className` passthrough are unverified. |\n| W4 | `integration-icon.tsx + test` | `alt` / `aria-hidden` contract is unasserted. The icon sits next to an already-visible type label, making it redundant — the right call is likely `aria-hidden=\"true\"` + `alt=\"\"`, but neither decision is pinned by a test. |\n| W5 | `integrations/page.tsx` (no test) | No page-level test exists. The Add-button reposition (out of `PageHeader.actions`, into the body row) is fully unprotected. `skills/page.test.tsx` exists for the equivalent surface — this is a pattern gap. |\n\n---\n\n### Suggestions\n\n| # | File | Finding |\n|---|------|---------|\n| S1 | `integration-icon.tsx:3-11` | `ICON_PATHS` is an untyped string map. Typing it as `Record\u003cIntegrationType, string\u003e` would make TS surface missing entries when a new backend integration type ships, instead of silently falling back to initials. |\n| S2 | `integration-icon.tsx:42-49` | `width={size}` / `height={size}` as HTML attrs on `\u003cimg\u003e`, but `style={{width,height}}` on the fallback `\u003cdiv\u003e`. Inconsistent between branches; align both to one approach. |\n| S3 | `integration-icon.test.tsx` | `loading=\"lazy\"` and `width`/`height` aren't asserted — these are part of the component's paint-performance contract. Add `toHaveAttribute('loading', 'lazy')` + `toHaveAttribute('width', '24')` to the happy-path test. |\n| S4 | `integration-icon.test.tsx` | Missing negative assertion in the fallback test: `expect(screen.queryByRole('img')).toBeNull()` — without it, the test doesn't confirm the two branches are actually divergent. |\n| S5 | `integration-card.test.tsx` | Add `expect(screen.getByRole('img', { name: 'github logo' })).toBeInTheDocument()` (or `getByAltText`) plus a negative assertion that the legacy two-letter badge text is gone. |\n| S6 | `public/integration-icons/notion.svg` | `fill=\"#000000\"` will be invisible on dark-chip backgrounds if theming is ever added. Not urgent, but document the hard dependency on the white chip wrapper in `integration-card.tsx:30` so it isn't removed carelessly. |\n\n---\n\n### What's clean\n\n- **SVG hygiene is good**: all 7 vendor assets have `viewBox`, `role=\"img\"`, `\u003ctitle\u003e`, no inline `\u003cscript\u003e`, no external refs, no baked `width`/`height` dimensions.\n- **PageHeader.actions removal is consistent**: none of the other 5 pages using `PageHeader` populate `actions` — this page is now aligned with the pattern, not an outlier.\n- **Icon test uses `it.each`** correctly for the happy path, matching the project's table-driven convention.\n- **`src` path resolution**: `/integration-icons/` is a Next.js `public/` path; no base-URL or import issues.\n\n---\n\n### Priority fixes before merge\n\n1. **(W1)** Add `role=\"img\"` to the fallback `\u003cdiv\u003e` in `IntegrationIcon`.\n2. **(W2)** Add an icon-presence assertion to `integration-card.test.tsx` — this is the single highest-value test fix.\n3. **(W4)** Decide the a11y contract (decorative `aria-hidden=\"true\"` + `alt=\"\"` is the right call given the adjacent type label) and lock it with an assertion.\n4. **(W5)** Add a minimal `integrations/page.test.tsx` asserting the Add button renders in the body (not the header) for both populated and empty-state branches.\n5. **(W3)** Parameterize the fallback `it.each` to cover `\"\"` and single-char types.\n",
