      "result": "\u003coutput\u003e\n{\n  \"rating\": 3,\n  \"summary\": \"Test for `integration-icon.tsx` is well structured (table-driven, semantic role queries) and covers happy-path + a single unknown-type fallback. However, three coverage gaps make the suite materially weak: `integration-card.test.tsx` was not updated to lock the badge→icon swap (the very behavior change in this PR), `gui/src/app/integrations/page.tsx` has no test at all so the Add-button reposition is unguarded, and the icon test omits several runtime edge cases (empty string, size/className prop passthrough, aria-hidden, loading=\\\"lazy\\\"). Solid happy-path discipline, but the diff's two non-icon behavior changes ship with zero regression nets.\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/integrations/integration-card.test.tsx:20-111\",\n      \"issue\": \"The PR's central card-level change is the TYPE_BADGES → IntegrationIcon swap, but this test file was not updated. Existing assertions (`getByText('github')`) still pass because they match the type label `\u003cspan\u003e`, not the removed badge — so reverting `\u003cIntegrationIcon ...\u003e` back to the two-letter badge would NOT fail any test. This is exactly the regression gap test #2 of the checklist asks about.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add an explicit assertion such as `expect(screen.getByRole('img', { name: 'github logo' })).toBeInTheDocument()` (or `getByAltText('github logo')`) inside the existing 'shows the integration name and type' test, and ideally a negative assertion that the legacy two-letter badge text (e.g. 'GI') is no longer rendered.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/app/integrations/page.tsx (no test file)\",\n      \"issue\": \"No `integrations/page.test.tsx` exists. The PR moves the Add Integration button out of `PageHeader.actions` and into the body row beside 'Configured Integrations (n)'. Nothing in the test suite would catch a regression that puts it back into the header, drops it on the configured branch, or breaks the empty-state CTA pluralization path. Compare with `gui/src/app/skills/page.test.tsx` which exists for the equivalent page-level surface — this is a pattern inconsistency, not a missing convention.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add a page test (with React Query / hooks mocked) that asserts: (a) when `integrations.length \u003e 0`, the 'Add Integration' button renders inside the row containing the 'Configured Integrations (N)' heading and NOT inside `PageHeader`; (b) the empty-state branch still renders the '+ Add your first integration' CTA; (c) clicking the body button opens the AddIntegrationModal.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/integrations/integration-icon.test.tsx:21-24\",\n      \"issue\": \"Fallback branch is covered by exactly one input ('custom'). Several real edge cases are unverified: empty string `type=\\\"\\\"` (renders an aria-label of ' icon' and zero-char text — arguably a bug), single-char `type=\\\"x\\\"` (slice(0,2) returns 'x'), and the `size` / `className` prop passthrough on the fallback `\u003cdiv\u003e` (style width/height and merged className). None are asserted.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Extend the `it.each` table to drive the fallback path too: `['', ''], ['x', 'x'], ['custom', 'cu']`. Add one test that passes a custom `size={48}` and asserts the rendered img has `width=\\\"48\\\"` and `height=\\\"48\\\"`, and one that passes `className=\\\"ring-2\\\"` and asserts it merges through on both branches.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/integrations/integration-icon.tsx:42-49 (and test:15-19)\",\n      \"issue\": \"Checklist item (c): the test never asserts `alt` directly nor `aria-hidden`. `getByRole('img', { name })` infers the accessible name from `alt`, which is fine, but the component does not set `aria-hidden` and the test doesn't pin that decision either way. Because the icon sits inside a card that ALSO renders the integration type text, the img is effectively redundant and an accessibility reviewer would likely want `aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\"` + `alt=\\\"\\\"`. Either way, the contract is not asserted.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Decide on the a11y contract and lock it: either assert `expect(img).toHaveAttribute('alt', \\\\`${type} logo\\\\`)` AND `expect(img).not.toHaveAttribute('aria-hidden')`, or change the component to `alt=\\\"\\\"` + `aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\"` and assert that. Don't leave it unasserted.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/integrations/integration-icon.test.tsx\",\n      \"issue\": \"Static attributes that the component intentionally sets — `loading=\\\"lazy\\\"`, `width={size}`, `height={size}` — are not asserted. These are part of the component contract (lazy loading impacts INP / paint behavior on a list page) and silently regressing them would not be caught.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add `expect(img).toHaveAttribute('loading', 'lazy')` and `expect(img).toHaveAttribute('width', '24')` to the happy-path test.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/integrations/integration-icon.test.tsx:21-24\",\n      \"issue\": \"Single fallback assertion uses `toHaveTextContent` but doesn't also confirm that `getByRole('img')` returns nothing on the fallback path — i.e., there's no negative assertion proving the component did NOT render an `\u003cimg\u003e`.\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Add `expect(screen.queryByRole('img')).toBeNull()` in the fallback test to lock branch divergence.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"severity\": \"suggestion\",\n      \"location\": \"gui/src/components/integrations/integration-icon.test.tsx:7-19\",\n      \"issue\": \"Checklist item (5): the icon test correctly uses `it.each`, matching project convention. No action needed — flagged here only to confirm the parametrize pattern is satisfied for the happy path. The fallback branch, however, is not parameterized (see W3 above).\",\n      \"suggestion\": \"Parameterize the fallback branch too so single-char, empty, and unknown types share one table.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"Add an icon-presence assertion to `integration-card.test.tsx` so the badge→icon swap is regression-protected (this is the single highest-value fix).\",\n    \"Create `gui/src/app/integrations/page.test.tsx` mirroring `skills/page.test.tsx`, asserting the Add button location in both empty and populated states.\",\n    \"Expand the icon fallback `it.each` to cover empty string and single-char types, and add explicit assertions for `size` / `className` / `loading=\\\"lazy\\\"` / accessibility attribute contracts.\",\n    \"Decide and pin the a11y contract for the decorative icon (likely `aria-hidden=\\\"true\\\"` + empty alt given the adjacent type label).\"\n  ],\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"files_reviewed\": 6,\n    \"domain\": \"test-coverage\"\n  }\n}\n\u003c/output\u003e",
